    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Catholic University of the Sacred Heart</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to compare the effects of six months treatment of two
      insulin-lowering therapies on the clinical and endocrine-metabolic parameters in obese women
      affected by polycystic ovary syndrome. The study group includes 40 patients, randomly
      allocated to subgroup A (metformin 1500 mg/day) and subgroup B (myo-inositol 1500 mg/day).
      The investigations include menstrual pattern and hirsutism score evaluation, hormonal assays,
      oral glucose tolerance test, euglycemic hyperinsulinaemic clamp and lipid profile at baseline
      and after six months of treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
